INSERT INTO `question`(`section`, `question_content`, `a`, `b`, `c`, `d`, `ans`, `sub_section`, `level`, `solution`, `date_posted`) VALUES ('Maths_finished files','A unit vector which is coplanar to vector \\({\\bf{i}} + {\\bf{j}} + 2k\\) and\\({\\bf{i}} + 2{\\bf{j}} + {\\bf{k}}\\) and perpendicular to \\({\\bf{i}} + {\\bf{j}} +{\\bf{k}},\\) is','\(a\)\\(\\frac{{{\\bf{i}} - {\\bf{j}}}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}\\)','\(b\)\\( \\pm \\,\\left({\\frac{{{\\bf{j}} - {\\bf{k}}}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}} \\right)\\)','\(c\)\\(\\frac{{{\\bf{k}} - {\\bf{i}}}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}\\)','\(d\)\\(\\frac{{{\\bf{i}} + {\\bf{j}} +{\\bf{k}}}}{{\\sqrt 3 }}\\)','2','VECTOR ALGEBRA','2','Answer = \(b\)Let the vector be given as \\(a{\\bf{i}} + b{\\bf{j}} + c{\\bf{k}}.\\) Forthis vector to be coplanar with \\({\\bf{i}} + {\\bf{j}} + 2{\\bf{k}}\\) and\\({\\bf{i}} + 2{\\bf{j}} + {\\bf{k}},\\) we will have \\(a{\\bf{i}} + b{\\bf{j}} +c{\\bf{k}} = p({\\bf{i}} + {\\bf{j}} + 2{\\bf{k}}) + r({\\bf{i}} + 2{\\bf{j}} +{\\bf{k}})\\)This gives,  \\(a = p + r\\).....(i)\\(b = p + 2r\\).....(ii)\\(c = 2p + r\\).....(iii)For the vector \\(a{\\bf{i}} + b{\\bf{j}} + c{\\bf{k}}\\) to be perpendicular to\\({\\bf{i}} + {\\bf{j}} + {\\bf{k}},\\) we will have \\((a{\\bf{i}} + b{\\bf{j}} +c{\\bf{k}})\\,.\\,({\\bf{i}} + {\\bf{j}} + {\\bf{k}}) = 0\\)\\( \\Rightarrow a + b + c = 0\\)     ......(iv)Adding equation (i) to (iii), we get \\(4p + 4r = a + b + c\\)\\(\\Rightarrow 4(p + r) = 0 \\Rightarrow p =  - r\\)Now with the help of (i), (ii) and (iii), we get\\(a = 0,\\) \\(b = r,\\)\\(c = p =  - r\\)Hence the required vector is \\(r({\\bf{j}} - {\\bf{k}})\\)To be its unit vector \\({r^2} + {r^2} = 1 \\Rightarrow r =  \\pm \\frac{1}{{\\sqrt 2}}\\)Hence the required unit vector is, \\( \\pm \\frac{1}{{\\sqrt 2 }}({\\bf{j}} -{\\bf{k}})\\).Trick : Check for option \\({\\rm{\(a\)}},\\,\\,\\frac{{{\\bf{i}} - {\\bf{j}}}}{{\\sqrt 2}}\\) is a unit vector and perpendicular to \\({\\bf{i}} + {\\bf{j}} + {\\bf{k}}\\).But \\(\\left| {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}{\\frac{1}{{\\sqrt 2 }}}&{\\frac{{ - 1}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}}&0\\\\1&1&2\\\\1&2&1\\end{array}} \\right| =  - \\frac{4}{{\\sqrt 2 }} \\ne 0\\).So it is not coplanar with the given vector.Check for option \\({\\rm{(b}}),\\,\\, \\pm \\left( {\\frac{{{\\bf{j}} -{\\bf{k}}}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}} \\right)\\) is a unit vector and also perpendicular to\\({\\bf{i}} + {\\bf{j}} + {\\bf{k}},\\) \\(\\left| {\\,\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}0&{\\frac{1}{{\\sqrt 2 }}}&{\\frac{{ - 1}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}}\\\\1&1&2\\\\1&2&1\\end{array}\\,} \\right| = 0\\).So, it is also coplanar with the given vectors.',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);
