INSERT INTO `question`(`section`, `question_content`, `a`, `b`, `c`, `d`, `ans`, `sub_section`, `level`, `solution`, `date_posted`) VALUES ('Maths_finished files','If the sum of \\(n\\) terms of an A.P. is \\(2{n^2} + 5n\\), then the\\({n^{th}}\\) term will be ','\(a\)\\(4n + 3\\)','\(b\)\\(4n + 5\\)','\(c\)\\(4n + 6\\)','\(d\)\\(4n + 7\\)','1','PROGRESSIONS','2','Answer = \(a\)Given that \\({S_n} = 2{n^2} + 5n\\)Putting \\(n = 1,\\;2,\\;3,\\;..........,\\;{S_1} = 2 \\times 1 + 5 \\times 1 = 7\\;\\),\\({S_2} = 2 \\times 4 + 10 = 8 + 10 = 18,\\;{S_3} = 18 + 15 = 33.\\)So, \\({T_1} = {S_1} = a = 7,\\;{T_2} = {S_2} - {S_1} = 18 - 7 = 11\\),\\({T_3} = {S_3} - {S_2} = 33 - 18 = 15\\)Therefore series is \\(7,\\,11,\\;15,\\,........\\)Now, \\({n^{th}}\\) term \\( = a + (n - 1)d = 7 + (n - 1)4 = 4n + 3\\).Aliter : As we know \\({T_n} = {S_n} - {S_{n - 1}}\\)\\(= (2{n^2} + 5n) - \\left\\{ {2\\,{{(n - 1)}^2} + 5\\,(n - 1)} \\right\\}\\)\\(= 2{n^2} + 5n - 2{n^2} + 4n - 2 - 5n + 5 = 4n + 3.\\)',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);
