INSERT INTO `question`(`section`, `question_content`, `a`, `b`, `c`, `d`, `ans`, `sub_section`, `level`, `solution`, `date_posted`) VALUES ('Maths_finished files','If A and B be any two sets, then \\((A \\cap B)\\'\\) is equal to','\(a\)\\(A\\' \\cap {\\rm B}\\'\\)\(b\)\\(A\\' \\cup B\\'\\)\(c\)\\(A \\cap B\\)\(d\)\\(A \\cup B\\)561. Let A and B  be subsets of a set X. Then','\(a\)\\(A - B = A \\cup B\\)\(b\)\\(A - B = A \\cap B\\)\(c\)\\(A - B = {A^c} \\cap B\\)\(d\)\\(A - B = A \\cap {B^c}\\)562. Let A and B be two sets in the universal set. Then \\(A - B\\) equals','\(a\)\\(A \\cap {B^c}\\)\(b\)\\({A^c} \\cap B\\)\(c\)\\(A \\cap B\\)\(d\)None of these563. If A, B and C are any three sets, then \\(A - (B \\cap C)\\) is equal to','\(a\)\\((A - B) \\cup (A - C)\\)\(b\)\\((A - B) \\cap (A - C)\\)\(c\)\\((A - B) \\cup C\\)\(d\)\\((A - B) \\cap C\\)564. If A, B, C are three sets, then A \\(\\cap{}\\) (B  \\(\\cup{}\\) C) is equal to\(a\)(A \\(\\cup{}\\) B) \\(\\cap{}\\) (A \\(\\cup{}\\) C)\(b\)(A \\(\\cap{}\\) B) \\(\\cup{}\\) (A\\(\\cap{}\\) C)\(c\)(A \\(\\cup{}\\) B) \\(\\cup{}\\) (A \\(\\cup{}\\) C)\(d\)None of these565. If A = {1, 2, 4}, B = {2, 4, 5}, C = {2, 5}, then (A - B) \\(\\times{}\\)(B - C) is\(a\){(1, 2), (1, 5), (2, 5)}\(b\){(1, 4)}\(c\)(1, 4)\(d\)None of these566. If (1, 3), (2, 5) and (3, 3) are three elements of A \\(\\times{}\\) B and thetotal number of elements in \\(A \\times B\\) is 6, then the remaining elements of \\(A \\times B\\) are\(a\)(1, 5); (2, 3); (3, 5)\(b\)(5, 1); (3, 2); (5, 3)\(c\)(1, 5); (2, 3); (5, 3)\(d\)None of these567. A = {1, 2, 3} and B = {3, 8}, then  (A \\(\\cup{}\\) B) \\(\\times{}\\) (A\\(\\cap{}\\) B) is\(a\){(3, 1), (3, 2), (3, 3), (3, 8)}\(b\){(1, 3), (2, 3), (3, 3), (8, 3)}\(c\){(1, 2), (2, 2), (3, 3), (8, 8)}\(d\){(8, 3), (8, 2), (8, 1), (8, 8)}568. If A = {2, 3, 5}, B = {2, 5, 6}, then (A - B) \\(\\times{}\\) (A \\(\\cap{}\\) B) is\(a\){(3, 2), (3, 3), (3, 5)}\(b\){(3, 2), (3, 5), (3, 6)}\(c\){(3, 2), (3, 5)}\(d\)None of these569. In a class of 30 pupils, 12 take needle work, 16take physics and 18 take history. If all the 30 students take at least onesubject and no one takes all three then the number of pupils taking 2 subjectsis\(a\)16\(b\)6\(c\)8\(d\)20','2','SETS  RELATIONS','2','Answer = \(b\)From De\\' morgan\\'s law, \\((A \\cap B)\\' = A\\' \\cup B\\'\\).',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);
INSERT INTO `question`(`section`, `question_content`, `a`, `b`, `c`, `d`, `ans`, `sub_section`, `level`, `solution`, `date_posted`) VALUES ('Maths_finished files','The number of elements in the set \\(\\{ (a,\\,b):2{a^2} + 3{b^2} = 35,\\;a,\\,b\\in Z\\} \\), where Z is the set of all integers, is','\(a\)2','\(b\)4','\(c\)8','\(d\)12(e)16','3','SETS  RELATIONS','2','Answer = \(c\)Given set is \\(\\{ (a,\\,b):2{a^2} + 3{b^2} = 35,\\;a,\\,b \\in Z\\} \\)We can see that, \\(2{( \\pm 2)^2} + 3{( \\pm 3)^2} = 35\\)and \\(2{( \\pm 4)^2} + 3{( \\pm 1)^2} = 35\\)\\(\\therefore{}\\) (2, 3), (2, -3), (-2, -3), (-2, 3), (4, 1), (4, -1),(-4, -1), (-4, 1) are 8 elements of the set. \\(\\therefore{}\\) \\(n = 8\\).',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);
